An environmentalist and fire service expert, Cliff Bisi Lawani, yesterday charged the new Comptroller-General of the Federal Fire Service, Lima Ibrahim, to immediately visit the fire service formations nationwide and carry out a turnaround. This, according to him, is to make the service meet the latest fire-fighting standard expected globally. He spoke with newsmen in Lagos on the appointment of new Fire Comptroller-General by President Muhammadu Buhari which described as a right step in the right direction. He observed that fire formations nationwide were facing a lot of challenges bothering on efficiency, saying they deserve urgent turnaround. Need for a functional fire service Fire Service partners NOA to fight emergencies Buhari extends FFS boss tenure